  "notes": "Jamaican Patois (Jumiekan Kryuol) written in the Cassidy/JLU orthography (Cassidy 1961; standardised by the Jamaican Language Unit, UWI Mona, 2002). Phonemic by design: short vowels i e a o u; long vowels doubled (ii, aa, uu); diphthongs <ie> <uo> <ai> <ou>; <ch>=/tʃ/, <j>=/dʒ/, <sh>=/ʃ/, <zh>=/ʒ/, <ng>=/ŋ/. Nasal vowels are written with a following -hn (e.g. kyaahn); that convention and the palatalised <ky>/<gy> onsets are not modelled here. /h/ is variable across Jamaica. Note: much Patois is also written in ad-hoc English-based spelling, which this spec does NOT cover — Cassidy/JLU input is assumed.",
